630
01:04:40,043 --> 01:04:41,204
(BETTY SCREAMS)

631
01:04:49,677 --> 01:04:50,792
(BETTY SCREAMS)

632
01:04:50,845 --> 01:04:52,131
(DOG SNARLING)

633
01:04:54,140 --> 01:04:55,505
(GROWLING)

634
01:04:58,812 --> 01:04:59,812
(GASPS)

635
01:05:00,563 --> 01:05:01,974
(GRUNTING)

636
01:05:08,279 --> 01:05:10,395
(HULK PANTING)

637
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:40,406
He sent these dogs, didn't he?

638
01:06:41,789 --> 01:06:43,496
But I killed them!

639
01:06:43,666 --> 01:06:45,498
(GRUNTING)

640
01:06:47,378 --> 01:06:48,413
(SCREAMING)

641
01:07:09,025 --> 01:07:10,265
My God.

642
01:07:10,860 --> 01:07:13,522
It must be the nanomeds.
It must be the gamma exposure.

643
01:07:13,613 --> 01:07:16,605
But we've never seen
any effect like this before.

644
01:07:16,699 --> 01:07:18,610
No. Deeper.

645
01:07:19,619 --> 01:07:22,236
The gamma just unleashed
what was already there.

646
01:07:22,288 --> 01:07:23,870
Unleashed what?

647
01:07:25,792 --> 01:07:26,873
Me.

648
01:07:28,211 --> 01:07:29,451
It.

649
01:07:29,963 --> 01:07:31,374
<i>(GASPING)</i>

650
01:07:32,131 --> 01:07:33,496
It's okay.

651
01:07:33,841 --> 01:07:35,206
It's okay.

652
01:07:36,970 --> 01:07:38,927
What were those animals?

653
01:07:40,223 --> 01:07:42,009
My father sent them.

654
01:07:42,976 --> 01:07:44,637
He is my father.

655
01:07:45,728 --> 01:07:47,639
He wanted me to change.

656
01:07:47,730 --> 01:07:50,768
He wanted me to change
into that mindless hulk.

657
01:07:51,234 --> 01:07:53,145
Why would he want that?

658
01:07:54,821 --> 01:07:56,858
Can you remember anything?

659
01:07:56,948 --> 01:07:59,861
Is there anything
from when you were changed?

660
01:08:03,162 --> 01:08:04,994
It was like a dream.

661
01:08:06,833 --> 01:08:08,198
About what?

662
01:08:10,461 --> 01:08:11,576
Rage.

663
01:08:14,048 --> 01:08:15,254
Power.

664
01:08:17,510 --> 01:08:18,921
And freedom.

665
01:08:36,696 --> 01:08:37,982
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

666
01:08:38,698 --> 01:08:41,315
Hello? Sir.

667
01:08:42,702 --> 01:08:44,488
Hello. Dad?

668
01:08:44,537 --> 01:08:46,528
Betty! Are you all right?

669
01:08:49,167 --> 01:08:52,660
I'm scared.
I need your help.

670
01:08:53,004 --> 01:08:54,540
Where are you?

671
01:09:05,224 --> 01:09:06,680
How are you?

672
01:09:07,727 --> 01:09:09,843
Okay, I guess.

673
01:09:14,067 --> 01:09:15,899
<i>I think that somehow</i>

674
01:09:16,736 --> 01:09:19,398
your anger is triggering
the nanomeds.

675
01:09:20,657 --> 01:09:24,275
How could it? We designed them
to respond to physical damage.

676
01:09:24,369 --> 01:09:27,157
Emotional damage
can manifest physically.

677
01:09:28,915 --> 01:09:30,246
Like what?

678
01:09:34,212 --> 01:09:35,748
Serious trauma.

679
01:09:38,299 --> 01:09:40,040
Repressed memories.

680
01:09:45,640 --> 01:09:50,430
Your father grilled me about something
that happened to me from early childhood

681
01:09:50,520 --> 01:09:52,761
that I'm supposed to remember.

682
01:09:53,272 --> 01:09:55,604
He did?
It sounded bad, but...

683
01:09:57,485 --> 01:09:59,522
I honestly don't remember.

684
01:10:02,699 --> 01:10:04,690
The thing that worries me

685
01:10:05,284 --> 01:10:06,284
is

686
01:10:07,370 --> 01:10:11,284
A physical wound is finite,
but with emotions,

687
01:10:11,457 --> 01:10:14,415
<i>what's to say it won't
just go on and on</i>

688
01:10:15,461 --> 01:10:17,577
and start a chain reaction?

689
01:10:21,217 --> 01:10:23,629
You know
what scares me the most?

690
01:10:25,763 --> 01:10:27,345
When it happens,

691
01:10:28,975 --> 01:10:32,764
when it comes over me
and I totally lose control,

692
01:10:35,940 --> 01:10:37,271
I like it.

693
01:10:42,739 --> 01:10:43,979
(BEEPING)

694
01:10:51,539 --> 01:10:52,654
(GASPS)

695
01:10:54,917 --> 01:10:57,659
It's okay. I got you.
I'm sorry.

696
01:10:58,921 --> 01:11:01,663
You'll be okay.
It's just to make you sleep.

697
01:11:01,758 --> 01:11:03,590
Target down. Target secure.

698
01:11:04,469 --> 01:11:06,380
I'm going to take you
some place safe.

699
01:11:06,471 --> 01:11:08,462
Okay? Bruce?

700
01:11:09,891 --> 01:11:11,097
Bruce?

701
01:11:12,393 --> 01:11:13,554
<i>Bruce?</i>

702
01:11:17,523 --> 01:11:19,059
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

703
01:13:49,133 --> 01:13:50,339
MAN: Clear!

704
01:13:56,515 --> 01:13:58,176
(RADIO CHATTERING)

705
01:14:00,311 --> 01:14:02,518
Attention on deck.
Carry on.

706
01:14:11,489 --> 01:14:13,947
BETTY: We're buried out here
in the middle of nowhere.

707
01:14:14,033 --> 01:14:16,024
How long are you
gonna keep him sedated?

708
01:14:16,118 --> 01:14:18,359
For the rest of his
natural life, if I have to.

709
01:14:18,454 --> 01:14:21,492
You said I could trust you.
I'm your father.

710
01:14:21,958 --> 01:14:26,202
<i>You can trust me to do what I think
is right, not what you think you want.</i>

711
01:14:26,253 --> 01:14:29,666
He is a human being.
He is also something else.

712
01:14:30,257 --> 01:14:33,716
Suppose he gets out, has
one of his little mood swings

713
01:14:33,803 --> 01:14:35,089
<i>in a populated area.</i>

714
01:14:35,179 --> 01:14:37,261
Yes, I'm aware of
the potential danger.

715
01:14:37,348 --> 01:14:39,715
I'm also aware that
he saved my life.

716
01:14:39,809 --> 01:14:42,267
Yeah, from a mutant
French poodle.

717
01:14:42,979 --> 01:14:45,220
I'm indebted to him for that.

718
01:14:45,314 --> 01:14:48,898
He also put three men in a
hospital, and Talbot's barely walking!

719
01:14:48,985 --> 01:14:52,319
What do you want me to do?
I want you to help him!

720
01:14:53,072 --> 01:14:54,858
Why is he such a threat to you?

721
01:14:54,907 --> 01:14:57,114
<i>Because I know
what he comes from.</i>

722
01:14:57,201 --> 01:15:01,240
He is his father's son,
every last molecule of him.

723
01:15:01,872 --> 01:15:03,909
He says he doesn't
know his father,

724
01:15:04,000 --> 01:15:08,415
<i>but he's workin' in the same
exact goddamn field his father did.</i>

725
01:15:09,588 --> 01:15:13,877
<i>So either he's lyin' or it's
somethin' worse, and he's...</i>

726
01:15:13,926 --> 01:15:15,087
What?

727
01:15:15,845 --> 01:15:18,963
<i>Predestined to follow
in his father's footsteps?</i>

728
01:15:21,350 --> 01:15:23,387
I was gonna say "damned.”

729
01:15:24,812 --> 01:15:26,598
Of course you were.

730
01:15:26,939 --> 01:15:27,974
But I'm a scientist.

731
01:15:28,065 --> 01:15:32,354
<i>As a scientist, I believe we can
figure this out and he can be helped.</i>

732
01:15:33,404 --> 01:15:34,894
I know you do.

733
01:15:36,449 --> 01:15:39,111
Whether you know or care,

734
01:15:40,786 --> 01:15:43,778
I've got a lot of pride
in what you've done.

735
01:15:44,165 --> 01:15:46,327
But this is too big for you.

736
01:15:46,792 --> 01:15:50,786
<i>Look, I know the government thinks
they have a weapon on their hands.</i>

737
01:15:50,880 --> 01:15:53,212
Otherwise, he'd be dead by now.

738
01:15:53,299 --> 01:15:55,381
They can probe and prod
all they want,

739
01:15:55,468 --> 01:15:57,675
and in the meanwhile,
just let me try to help him.

740
01:15:57,762 --> 01:16:00,220
<i>Nobody knows him
better than I do.</i>

741
01:16:04,310 --> 01:16:06,722
What did David Banner do to him?

742
01:16:11,192 --> 01:16:13,149
Cover left.
Clear left.

743
01:16:13,235 --> 01:16:14,270
Cover right!

744
01:16:14,320 --> 01:16:15,526
(SIREN WAILING)

745
01:16:15,613 --> 01:16:16,978
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

746
01:16:48,145 --> 01:16:50,102
(AIR HISSING)

747
01:16:56,028 --> 01:16:58,235
(INHALING)

748
01:17:02,493 --> 01:17:03,654
(GRUNTING)

749
01:17:05,871 --> 01:17:07,532
(HEART BEATING)

750
01:17:50,749 --> 01:17:51,910
(CLINKING)

751
01:17:55,254 --> 01:17:56,870
(CREAKING)

752
01:18:25,701 --> 01:18:27,612
What's happening here?

753
01:18:28,704 --> 01:18:29,944
My hand.

754
01:18:32,458 --> 01:18:35,746
You see, the strength
of my son's DNA

755
01:18:37,379 --> 01:18:41,213
combined with nanomed
reconstruction...

756
01:18:43,594 --> 01:18:47,087
<i>You see, I can partake with
the essences of all things.</i>

757
01:18:49,475 --> 01:18:51,466
Gonna have to ask you to

758
01:18:51,977 --> 01:18:54,218
put your hands up, pal, okay?

759
01:18:55,147 --> 01:18:56,637
Nice and easy.

760
01:19:00,194 --> 01:19:01,480
(WHEEZING LAUGH)

761
01:19:03,405 --> 01:19:08,150
<i>Do you really believe
that I am separate from you?</i>

762
01:19:09,078 --> 01:19:10,193
(LAUGHS)

763
01:19:10,621 --> 01:19:11,736
Whoa!

764
01:19:12,831 --> 01:19:14,117
(GRUNTING)

765
01:19:27,346 --> 01:19:28,711
Where am I?

766
01:19:33,519 --> 01:19:34,975
You're home.

767
01:19:47,700 --> 01:19:50,567
It's hard to believe
we used to live here.

768
01:19:52,871 --> 01:19:55,533
I must have seen you
or known you.

769
01:19:56,375 --> 01:19:58,366
If only I could remember.

770
01:20:32,870 --> 01:20:35,202
This is my old house, isn't it?

771
01:21:15,329 --> 01:21:16,615
Let's go.

772
01:21:18,290 --> 01:21:19,655
Please try.

773
01:22:00,707 --> 01:22:02,698
(SHUDDERING)

774
01:22:14,179 --> 01:22:17,092
BETTY: What is it?
Nothing.

775
01:22:19,101 --> 01:22:20,341
Really?

776
01:22:23,397 --> 01:22:24,683
Damn it.

777
01:22:30,028 --> 01:22:31,439
Okay, Betty.

778
01:22:33,031 --> 01:22:35,068
What do you want to know?

779
01:22:37,536 --> 01:22:39,402
<i>What was in that room?</i>

780
01:22:50,632 --> 01:22:53,090
What are you afraid
that I'll see?

781
01:22:53,177 --> 01:22:54,258
(GASPS)

782
01:22:59,057 --> 01:23:01,845
See? There's nothing.

783
01:23:03,896 --> 01:23:05,307
It's empty.

784
01:23:18,076 --> 01:23:20,283
BETTY: What do you
mean I don't have access to him?

785
01:23:20,370 --> 01:23:23,783
NSA has decided
to turn over study

786
01:23:24,041 --> 01:23:26,157
of the threat to Atheon.

787
01:23:27,628 --> 01:23:31,246
But you're head of the base.
I thought you were in charge.

788
01:23:31,340 --> 01:23:34,753
<i>But I don't set policy,
and I still take orders.</i>

789
01:23:35,677 --> 01:23:36,792
(YELLS)

790
01:23:38,222 --> 01:23:41,556
I can't believe Talbot
would go around me like this!

791
01:23:43,727 --> 01:23:47,391
Oh, there's a lot of powerful
people that want in on this.

792
01:23:47,648 --> 01:23:50,185
And money to be made,
lots of it.

793
01:23:55,989 --> 01:23:58,777
You know the worst part
about all this?

794
01:23:59,785 --> 01:24:02,277
When I had David Banner
locked up and sent that kid away,

795
01:24:02,371 --> 01:24:06,410
<i>I didn't give that boy a second
thought. He was just collateral damage.</i>

796
01:24:06,792 --> 01:24:09,079
Well, he isn't anymore, is he?

797
01:24:12,464 --> 01:24:14,000
What can I do?

798
01:24:16,009 --> 01:24:17,795
You can go home now.

799
01:24:19,638 --> 01:24:22,972
I'd tell you to go and say good-bye,
but I've already been informed

800
01:24:23,058 --> 01:24:26,642
that for now all further
contact is out of the question.

801
01:24:28,063 --> 01:24:29,224
Right.

802
01:24:56,633 --> 01:24:57,873
(DOOR OPENING)

803
01:24:59,970 --> 01:25:01,085
(DOOR CLOSING)

804
01:25:08,103 --> 01:25:12,017
Hiya, Bruce. How ya feelin'?
Grub okay in here for ya?

805
01:25:13,483 --> 01:25:16,350
What do you want?
That's a good question.

806
01:25:17,529 --> 01:25:21,568
See, I need your cells to trigger
some chemical distress signals.

807
01:25:22,034 --> 01:25:25,447
You know, so you can turn
a little green for me again,

808
01:25:25,787 --> 01:25:28,745
<i>and I can carve off
a piece of the real you,</i>

809
01:25:29,374 --> 01:25:32,036
analyze it, patent it,
make a fortune.

810
01:25:33,712 --> 01:25:35,077
Do you mind?

811
01:25:36,173 --> 01:25:37,914
I'll never let you.

812
01:25:38,675 --> 01:25:41,212
I'm not sure you've got
much of a choice.

813
01:25:41,303 --> 01:25:42,543
(SCREAMS)

814
01:25:43,013 --> 01:25:45,675
Come on, Bruce. Aren't
you feeling a little angry?

815
01:25:45,807 --> 01:25:47,410
After all, you've only got
me to play with

816
01:25:47,434 --> 01:25:49,641
<i>now that Betty's dumped you
and gone back to Berkeley.</i>

817
01:25:49,728 --> 01:25:50,843
(SCREAMS)

818
01:25:50,896 --> 01:25:52,136
You're lying.

819
01:25:52,230 --> 01:25:54,938
<i>You know, for me
this is a win-win situation.</i>

820
01:25:55,025 --> 01:25:57,562
You turn green, and all these
guys come in and kill you,

821
01:25:57,653 --> 01:25:59,143
<i>and I perform the autopsy.</i>

822
01:25:59,237 --> 01:26:01,483
You don't... (SCREAMS)

823
01:26:02,824 --> 01:26:04,189
And I mop the floor with you

824
01:26:04,242 --> 01:26:07,075
and maybe by accident go
too far and break your neck.

825
01:26:07,245 --> 01:26:11,534
Bad science, maybe,
but personally gratifying.

826
01:26:11,750 --> 01:26:13,081
(SCREAMS)

827
01:26:13,960 --> 01:26:17,453
Come on, Bruce!
Let's see what you got.

828
01:26:17,589 --> 01:26:18,829
(PANTING)

829
01:26:19,174 --> 01:26:20,380
Never.

830
01:26:22,511 --> 01:26:23,922
(GRUNTING)

831
01:26:26,431 --> 01:26:29,264
You know, consciously
you may control it,

832
01:26:29,518 --> 01:26:32,601
<i>but subconsciously,
I bet that's another story.</i>

833
01:27:02,718 --> 01:27:05,801
All right, let's jump-start
those brain waves.

834
01:27:05,887 --> 01:27:07,218
(RADIO CHATTERING)

835
01:27:07,305 --> 01:27:08,887
(HUMMING)

836
01:27:10,851 --> 01:27:12,512
(EDITH CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

837
01:27:17,023 --> 01:27:18,229
EDITH: Bruce.

838
01:27:32,372 --> 01:27:35,535
(GASPS)
My dear Miss Ross.
Welcome back.

839
01:27:36,835 --> 01:27:38,951
There are two guards
right outside.

840
01:27:39,004 --> 01:27:43,339
You don't have to worry. I'm
not angry with you. Not anymore.

841
01:27:45,177 --> 01:27:46,667
What do you want?

842
01:27:46,720 --> 01:27:49,508
It's over for me now.
I know that.

843
01:27:50,182 --> 01:27:52,844
And soon it'll be
over for Bruce.

844
01:27:54,436 --> 01:27:56,177
That's why I've come to you

845
01:27:56,271 --> 01:27:59,855
to ask you if you could
persuade your father,

846
01:28:00,692 --> 01:28:03,104
as a man, as a father himself,

847
01:28:04,404 --> 01:28:07,863
that if I turn myself in now,
peacefully

848
01:28:08,408 --> 01:28:10,945
and before
he puts me away forever,

849
01:28:11,536 --> 01:28:14,028
that he would let me see my son

850
01:28:14,790 --> 01:28:16,497
for one last time.

851
01:28:17,417 --> 01:28:19,454
Could you do that for me?

852
01:28:22,881 --> 01:28:25,373
It's out of
my father's hands now.

853
01:28:30,222 --> 01:28:33,135
<i>I understand.
He's a puppet now.</i>

854
01:28:34,893 --> 01:28:37,385
I don't blame him.
You shouldn't.

855
01:28:37,562 --> 01:28:41,305
You should blame yourself for
what you've done to your son.

856
01:28:41,900 --> 01:28:45,188
And what have I done to
my son, Miss Ross? Nothing.

857
01:28:45,862 --> 01:28:49,480
I tried to improve
on the limits in myself.

858
01:28:50,075 --> 01:28:52,282
Myself! Not him!

859
01:28:52,953 --> 01:28:56,162
Can you understand?
To improve on nature.

860
01:28:56,248 --> 01:28:58,910
My nature!
Knowledge of oneself!

861
01:28:59,084 --> 01:29:01,416
It's the only path to the truth

862
01:29:01,837 --> 01:29:06,126
that give men the power
to go beyond God's boundaries!

863
01:29:07,217 --> 01:29:10,710
You know what's beyond
your boundaries? Other people.

864
01:29:12,264 --> 01:29:14,596
All you've given Bruce is fear.

865
01:29:16,977 --> 01:29:18,513
Fear of life.

866
01:29:21,940 --> 01:29:23,055
Fear?

867
01:29:25,277 --> 01:29:27,018
Perhaps, Miss Ross.

868
01:29:29,489 --> 01:29:31,230
And loneliness, too.

869
01:29:32,158 --> 01:29:33,364
Yes.

870
01:29:35,203 --> 01:29:36,864
I feel them both.

871
01:29:40,208 --> 01:29:44,793
<i>But I have lived
completely once.</i>

872
01:29:47,132 --> 01:29:49,043
<i>DAVID: I was so much in love,</i>

873
01:29:50,343 --> 01:29:52,801
and she so much wanted a baby.

874
01:29:53,221 --> 01:29:54,461
My baby.

875
01:30:02,689 --> 01:30:05,556
<i>I could tell
from the moment she conceived</i>

876
01:30:05,734 --> 01:30:08,317
<i>that it wasn't a son
I had given her</i>

877
01:30:08,737 --> 01:30:10,523
but something else.

878
01:30:11,281 --> 01:30:12,942
A monster, maybe.

879
01:30:13,241 --> 01:30:16,108
I should have put
a stop to it right then,

880
01:30:16,244 --> 01:30:20,203
<i>but I was curious,
and that was my downfall.</i>

881
01:30:21,333 --> 01:30:24,621
<i>And as I watched
this tiny life unfold,</i>

882
01:30:25,003 --> 01:30:28,212
I began to imagine
the horror of it,

883
01:30:28,548 --> 01:30:31,916
and my curiosity was replaced

884
01:30:33,178 --> 01:30:34,794
with compassion.

885
01:30:37,682 --> 01:30:40,174
DAVID: But they took away
my chance to cure him.

886
01:30:40,226 --> 01:30:42,263
Your father threw me out.

887
01:30:43,396 --> 01:30:46,514
<i>EDITH: What are you doing?
I remember that day so well,</i>

888
01:30:46,608 --> 01:30:51,023
every moment, every sensation
walking into the house,

889
01:30:51,488 --> 01:30:54,697
the feeling of the handle
of the knife in my hand.

890
01:30:55,158 --> 01:31:00,073
<i>I knew I was doing a father's
work, fulfilling a father's mercy.</i>

891
01:31:00,580 --> 01:31:03,038
EDITH: (YELLING)
David, please stop it! No!

892
01:31:03,249 --> 01:31:05,707
David, no! Talk to me! Listen!

893
01:31:06,544 --> 01:31:08,581
But then she surprised me.

894
01:31:09,339 --> 01:31:11,125
(YELLING)

895
01:31:11,216 --> 01:31:13,378
EDITH: No! No!

896
01:31:13,635 --> 01:31:15,000
David, no!

897
01:31:15,553 --> 01:31:17,089
DAVID: It was as if

898
01:31:17,889 --> 01:31:20,551
she and the knife

899
01:31:22,018 --> 01:31:23,224
merged.

900
01:31:33,405 --> 01:31:34,645
No!

901
01:31:34,739 --> 01:31:37,071
You cannot imagine

902
01:31:37,742 --> 01:31:40,905
the unbearable finality of it.

903
01:31:42,539 --> 01:31:44,701
And in that one moment,

904
01:31:45,375 --> 01:31:48,584
<i>I took everything
that was dear to me</i>

905
01:31:49,671 --> 01:31:53,539
and transformed it
into nothing more

906
01:31:54,217 --> 01:31:55,753
than a memory.

907
01:32:11,609 --> 01:32:14,897
Bingo! That must be some
jumbo nightmare he just had.

908
01:32:19,617 --> 01:32:21,858
Okay, do it now.
Start the enzyme extraction.

909
01:32:23,705 --> 01:32:25,070
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

910
01:32:27,125 --> 01:32:29,162
Sir, negative
on drill penetration.

911
01:32:29,252 --> 01:32:31,289
Damn it, drill him harder!
Give him full RPMs.

912
01:32:31,337 --> 01:32:32,953
Come on, Holeman! Come on!

913
01:32:35,633 --> 01:32:37,249
(GROWLING)

914
01:32:43,975 --> 01:32:45,557
(MACHINE BEEPING)

915
01:32:46,978 --> 01:32:49,561
Should I neutralize?
No! I can't do anything with goop!

916
01:32:49,647 --> 01:32:50,887
Come on!

917
01:32:59,949 --> 01:33:01,064
(ROARING)

918
01:33:04,162 --> 01:33:06,324
All right, put him to sleep.

919
01:33:15,840 --> 01:33:17,751
TECHNICIAN:
It's not stopping him!

920
01:33:18,927 --> 01:33:20,167
(GROWLS)

921
01:33:24,557 --> 01:33:26,844
Ready room, send in
our containment team.

922
01:33:26,935 --> 01:33:30,144
<i>Non-lethals only.
I repeat, non-lethals only.</i>

923
01:33:30,188 --> 01:33:32,145
I must have a sample of him.

924
01:33:32,190 --> 01:33:33,305
WOMAN: Sir!

925
01:33:36,027 --> 01:33:39,236
Jesus!
Hit him with the foam.

926
01:33:39,364 --> 01:33:41,355
TECHNICIAN:
Deploy containment foam.

927
01:33:42,200 --> 01:33:43,986
Talbot, talk to me.

928
01:33:45,912 --> 01:33:46,912
<i>Cease fire!</i>

929
01:33:46,996 --> 01:33:49,283
Under control, General. I'll
let you know if we need you.

930
01:33:49,374 --> 01:33:52,207
Unacceptable. Unseat your
asses down there immediately.

931
01:33:52,252 --> 01:33:55,165
I want a full-court evacuation
now. I'm shutting you down.

932
01:33:55,213 --> 01:33:56,419
<i>Lock-down.</i>

933
01:33:56,923 --> 01:34:00,132
Didn't you hear what the
General said? I said lock-down!

934
01:34:02,428 --> 01:34:04,715
<i>Clear! I need a sample of him!</i>

935
01:34:06,933 --> 01:34:08,469
(GROWLING)

936
01:34:08,560 --> 01:34:10,597
Take it easy there, buddy.

937
01:34:10,728 --> 01:34:13,390
This might give you
a bit of a sting here, Bruce.

938
01:34:13,481 --> 01:34:14,562
(DRILL WHIRRS)

939
01:34:14,607 --> 01:34:16,223
(GROWLING)

940
01:34:24,159 --> 01:34:26,366
(GROWLING)

941
01:34:26,411 --> 01:34:29,403
Fall back! Fall back!
Clear your weapon! Clear it!

942
01:34:29,497 --> 01:34:32,831
Give me the M2.
So long, big boy.

943
01:34:33,626 --> 01:34:34,787
Clear!

944
01:34:35,086 --> 01:34:36,827
(GROWLING)

945
01:34:39,716 --> 01:34:41,707
(SCREAMING)

946
01:34:45,763 --> 01:34:48,630
Lock-down the entire
facility immediately.

947
01:34:53,062 --> 01:34:55,599
Target's still moving
towards blue level.

948
01:34:55,690 --> 01:34:57,601
Evacuate the main hall.

949
01:34:57,692 --> 01:34:59,353
(ALL SCREAMING)

950
01:35:02,071 --> 01:35:03,653
(GROWLING)

951
01:35:03,740 --> 01:35:07,199
Send in backup, heavy weapons.
Issue general quarters.

952
01:35:07,702 --> 01:35:09,488
Set firing lines left and right!

953
01:35:09,746 --> 01:35:12,454
Heavy weapons, go, go, go!

954
01:35:21,716 --> 01:35:23,172
<i>(MACHINE GUNS FIRING)</i>

955
01:35:30,850 --> 01:35:32,432
(MEN SHOUTING)

956
01:35:34,646 --> 01:35:36,808
Contamination, sir.
System readings are redline.

957
01:35:36,898 --> 01:35:39,139
Data's on backup power supply.

958
01:35:39,234 --> 01:35:40,816
(ALARM BLARING)

959
01:35:46,241 --> 01:35:47,447
Incoming!

960
01:35:47,700 --> 01:35:48,986
(ROARING)

961
01:35:49,494 --> 01:35:51,030
(MEN GASPING)

962
01:35:55,208 --> 01:35:57,950
Shut down all power
to the main hall.
Sir?

963
01:35:58,002 --> 01:36:01,290
Show him the way out.
We'll fight him outside.

964
01:36:44,299 --> 01:36:45,835
(MEN CHATTERING)

965
01:38:11,135 --> 01:38:13,797
Driver, stop. Driver, stop.

966
01:38:21,145 --> 01:38:23,762
COMMANDER: Gunner,
traverse left! Traverse left!

967
01:38:27,652 --> 01:38:28,858
(GRUNTING)

968
01:38:36,828 --> 01:38:39,195
(SCREAMING)

969
01:38:39,956 --> 01:38:42,197
(GRUNTING)

970
01:38:55,680 --> 01:38:56,886
(ROARING)

971
01:39:00,852 --> 01:39:02,593
(MEN GASPING)

972
01:39:06,983 --> 01:39:08,894
Clear back! Clear back!

973
01:39:14,615 --> 01:39:16,356
(GROANING)

974
01:39:22,039 --> 01:39:23,575
(GROWLING)

975
01:39:24,208 --> 01:39:25,539
(GRUNTING)

976
01:39:43,144 --> 01:39:44,600
(GRUNTING)

977
01:40:02,914 --> 01:40:06,123
Mr. President,
I have some bad news, sir.

978
01:40:06,751 --> 01:40:08,537
Let's have it, General.

979
01:40:08,586 --> 01:40:10,327
I've briefed the President
on Angry Man.

980
01:40:10,421 --> 01:40:11,911
I assume that's what
this is about.

981
01:40:12,006 --> 01:40:13,246
It is, ma'am.

982
01:40:13,341 --> 01:40:16,550
I'm requesting a National
Command Authority override.

983
01:40:16,594 --> 01:40:19,006
Angry Man is unsecure.

984
01:40:19,680 --> 01:40:24,049
I need everything we have at my
disposal in order to stop his movement.

985
01:40:24,268 --> 01:40:27,260
You're expecting
civilian casualties, General?

986
01:40:27,355 --> 01:40:29,517
<i>Not if I can help it, ma'am.</i>

987
01:40:29,732 --> 01:40:32,144
Consider it done.
Keep us posted.

988
01:41:20,825 --> 01:41:22,816
Contact Goodman Control.

989
01:41:22,952 --> 01:41:24,989
ROSS:
Patch data to the assets.

990
01:41:25,371 --> 01:41:26,827
Contact H.Q.

991
01:41:27,790 --> 01:41:30,999
<i>Have them initiate
an immediate evacuation</i>

992
01:41:31,627 --> 01:41:34,710
in vicinity of grid coordinates 6-5-15.

993
01:41:45,725 --> 01:41:46,725
(GRUNTS)

994
01:42:11,417 --> 01:42:13,499
Confirm that the area
has been cleared.

995
01:42:13,544 --> 01:42:15,205
Confirm area cleared.

996
01:42:15,296 --> 01:42:18,709
<i>MAN ON RADIO: H.Q. confirms
area cleared. Assets on-line, sir.</i>

997
01:42:18,758 --> 01:42:21,045
ROSS: Gentlemen,
it's time to dig in.

998
01:42:21,093 --> 01:42:24,131
I want this target
stopped in his tracks.

999
01:43:15,272 --> 01:43:16,433
Jesus.

1000
01:43:32,289 --> 01:43:35,156
Mayday! Mayday! Ah, shit!

1001
01:43:37,294 --> 01:43:38,750
(HULK GRUNTING)

1002
01:43:40,881 --> 01:43:44,840
TANGO ONE: Tango Four is down.
Have CSAR respond to our 20 ASAP.

1003
01:43:46,011 --> 01:43:49,174
TANGO FOUR: We're okay, but, damn it,
get him off us before he tears us apart!

1004
01:43:49,265 --> 01:43:51,848
TANGO ONE: I've got no shot.
Do you have a clear line of fire?

1005
01:43:52,685 --> 01:43:54,141
ROSS: Watch it, Tango Flight.

1006
01:43:54,186 --> 01:43:56,644
TANGO ONE:
Break left! Break left!

1007
01:43:57,815 --> 01:44:00,307
MAN: Tango Three, pull back
and set up for a Hellfire shot.

1008
01:44:00,359 --> 01:44:02,726
ROSS: Hold your fire
till we draw him off,

1009
01:44:02,987 --> 01:44:05,103
TANGO ONE:
Tango One is hot. Gun wazzed.

1010
01:44:05,197 --> 01:44:07,438
TANGO TWO: Roger.
Going hot. Guns ready.

1011
01:44:08,451 --> 01:44:09,816
(SNARLING)

1012
01:44:11,829 --> 01:44:12,910
(GRUNTS)

1013
01:44:12,997 --> 01:44:14,533
ROSS: Engage at will.

1014
01:44:21,005 --> 01:44:22,587
(GROWLING)

1015
01:44:35,352 --> 01:44:37,889
TANGO TWO: Tango One,
pull back! Clear my line!

1016
01:44:38,105 --> 01:44:41,018
TANGO THREE: Tango Flight, clear
back. I've got him painted for Hellfire.

1017
01:44:41,108 --> 01:44:42,473
Roger that.

1018
01:44:43,694 --> 01:44:46,026
Tango One clear.
Take the shot.

1019
01:45:04,882 --> 01:45:07,214
<i>TANGO THREE: Tango One,
Tango Three. I have contact.</i>

1020
01:45:07,635 --> 01:45:09,967
Holy shit!
He's got my missile!

1021
01:45:11,889 --> 01:45:13,425
Mayday! Mayday!

1022
01:45:16,018 --> 01:45:19,556
Mayday! Mayday! We're hit!
We're going down!

1023
01:45:23,400 --> 01:45:24,982
Give me a head count.

1024
01:45:25,069 --> 01:45:27,561
TANGO TWO: Tango Three,
give me a sit rep.

1025
01:45:28,155 --> 01:45:31,068
TANGO THREE: Our kite's
busted up, but we're okay.

1026
01:45:33,035 --> 01:45:35,493
ROSS: Tango Flight, do
you have eyes on the target?

1027
01:45:36,622 --> 01:45:38,659
<i>Tango One.
I have him in the rocks.</i>

1028
01:45:38,749 --> 01:45:41,366
ROSS: Salvo all.
Turn it into a parking lot.

1029
01:46:02,606 --> 01:46:04,688
TANGO ONE: T-bolt,
your parking lot is ready.

1030
01:46:04,775 --> 01:46:07,392
We're bingo
for fuel and ammo. R.T.B.

1031
01:46:24,044 --> 01:46:26,160
(PANTING)

1032
01:46:34,972 --> 01:46:36,852
WOMAN ON RADIO: T-bolt,
this is Goodman Control.

1033
01:46:36,891 --> 01:46:40,475
Be advised, target not
destroyed. He's on the move again.

1034
01:46:40,811 --> 01:46:41,972
Damn!

1035
01:46:42,521 --> 01:46:43,932
I've got it.

1036
01:46:44,899 --> 01:46:47,106
It appears he's heading home.

1037
01:46:47,985 --> 01:46:51,649
Launch fast movers. Have
them intercept and engage.

1038
01:46:52,990 --> 01:46:54,355
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1039
01:46:54,450 --> 01:46:55,565
Hello?

1040
01:46:55,659 --> 01:46:57,616
Betty, Bruce got out.

1041
01:46:57,661 --> 01:47:00,824
He's headed your way
and probably right for you.

1042
01:47:00,873 --> 01:47:02,864
How far from the base are you?

1043
01:47:02,958 --> 01:47:06,076
I'm already here. They're
taking his father in now.

1044
01:47:06,712 --> 01:47:09,830
That's all good news.
Stay there, Betty.

1045
01:47:24,146 --> 01:47:27,013
PILOT: Legend One rolling in
hot. Legend Two breaking off left.

1046
01:47:27,733 --> 01:47:30,851
<i>I think I can come back around
for a gun attack.</i>

1047
01:47:31,236 --> 01:47:33,853
ROSS: Acquire a clear target.
Fire at will.

1048
01:47:36,951 --> 01:47:38,032
(GRUNTS)

1049
01:47:39,036 --> 01:47:42,279
Increase altitude.
Civilian aircraft in vicinity.

1050
01:47:47,086 --> 01:47:50,204
Pull up! Pull up!
You're headed for the bridge!

1051
01:47:50,297 --> 01:47:51,662
(SCREAMING)

1052
01:47:51,882 --> 01:47:54,294
<i>I can't pull up!
I can't pull up!</i>

1053
01:48:02,810 --> 01:48:05,893
Okay, you've got him now. Take
him on a ride to the top of the world.

1054
01:48:05,980 --> 01:48:08,893
Let's see what the thin air
will do for him.

1055
01:48:09,650 --> 01:48:11,561
PILOT: Initiating after-burn.

1056
01:48:28,752 --> 01:48:32,370
I'm passing flight level 600.
This is out of my envelope.

1057
01:48:33,549 --> 01:48:35,005
ROSS: Hang in there, Legend.

1058
01:48:35,134 --> 01:48:38,252
I can't maintain.
He's all over my aerodynamics.

1059
01:48:38,345 --> 01:48:40,507
<i>He'll lose consciousness
before you.</i>

1060
01:48:44,518 --> 01:48:49,354
Nine-fifty. I can't hold it.
I'm pulling back!

1061
01:48:56,947 --> 01:48:58,312
(SCREAMING)

1062
01:49:36,904 --> 01:49:38,645
Puny human.

1063
01:49:47,706 --> 01:49:50,994
PILOT: Contact. He's in the
water. All units, weapons hot.

1064
01:49:51,168 --> 01:49:53,125
<i>ROSS: Let's not take any chances.</i>

1065
01:49:53,170 --> 01:49:56,037
You are cleared to fire
on target, Legend.

1066
01:50:05,432 --> 01:50:06,843
(RADIO CHATTERING)

1067
01:50:18,570 --> 01:50:20,026
BETTY: Dad?
Betty?

1068
01:50:21,406 --> 01:50:22,646
We don't have a choice.

1069
01:50:22,699 --> 01:50:24,690
I have to destroy him.

1070
01:50:24,827 --> 01:50:25,942
But you can't.

1071
01:50:26,036 --> 01:50:29,529
You will only fuel his rage,
and you will make him stronger.

1072
01:50:30,290 --> 01:50:33,032
It's you he's coming for.
You know that.

1073
01:50:35,045 --> 01:50:36,911
Then let me go to him.

1074
01:50:37,798 --> 01:50:39,038
Please.

1075
01:50:41,009 --> 01:50:43,546
Just give him a chance
to calm down.

1076
01:50:53,647 --> 01:50:55,137
(TRAM BELL RINGING)

1077
01:50:57,025 --> 01:50:58,436
(PASSENGERS SCREAMING)

1078
01:51:03,115 --> 01:51:07,825
ROSS: All aircraft vicinity of San
Francisco, this is T-bolt on guard.

1079
01:51:08,245 --> 01:51:11,328
This area has been declared
restricted airspace.

1080
01:51:11,748 --> 01:51:15,582
All aircraft are ordered to
clear the airspace immediately.

1081
01:51:18,422 --> 01:51:19,583
(CAR ALARM BLARING)

1082
01:51:22,384 --> 01:51:23,749
(ROARING)

1083
01:51:41,028 --> 01:51:42,268
(GROWLING)

1084
01:51:57,794 --> 01:51:59,606
MAN ON RADIO: Echo, One-niner.
Weapons are hot.

1085
01:51:59,630 --> 01:52:02,122
Target acquired.
Waiting your order to engage.

1086
01:52:02,216 --> 01:52:04,878
Repeat,
waiting your orders to engage.

1087
01:52:05,219 --> 01:52:08,132
PILOT: Command code yellow.
Hold for authorization.

1088
01:52:18,273 --> 01:52:20,014
All units, hold your fire.

1089
01:52:20,108 --> 01:52:22,003
TECHNICIAN ON RADIO:
This is T-bolt to all assets.

1090
01:52:22,027 --> 01:52:23,546
You have direct orders
to hold your fire.

1091
01:52:23,570 --> 01:52:25,811
<i>I repeat, hold your fire.</i>

1092
01:52:25,989 --> 01:52:27,730
PILOT: Echo, One-niner.
Roger that.

1093
01:52:31,870 --> 01:52:33,531
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

1094
01:52:42,589 --> 01:52:44,455
Go, go, go, go, go, go!

1095
01:52:44,508 --> 01:52:46,090
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1096
01:52:54,685 --> 01:52:56,346
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1097
01:53:13,829 --> 01:53:16,196
OFFICER: Hold your fire
until my command!

1098
01:53:19,668 --> 01:53:22,160
MAN ON RADIO: Engine 24 to
command. We are in position now.

1099
01:54:29,780 --> 01:54:31,270
You found me.

1100
01:54:33,784 --> 01:54:36,071
You weren't that hard to find.

1101
01:54:38,288 --> 01:54:39,653
Yes, I was.

1102
01:54:59,559 --> 01:55:00,970
(POLICE RADIO CHATTERING)

1103
01:55:28,213 --> 01:55:29,499
(SOBBING)

1104
01:55:40,100 --> 01:55:41,511
(DOOR OPENING)

1105
01:55:45,856 --> 01:55:47,517
Let's take a walk.

1106
01:56:19,556 --> 01:56:22,844
That's the deal, gentlemen.
He stays on this base

1107
01:56:22,893 --> 01:56:26,227
until we get the final word from
C-3 on how to dispose of him.

1108
01:56:27,314 --> 01:56:31,353
In the meantime, if he does
anything but sit there in that chair,

1109
01:56:32,986 --> 01:56:36,399
we're gonna turn on the juice
and he'll be incinerated immediately.

1110
01:56:36,490 --> 01:56:39,232
We've established
a 200-yard perimeter, sir.

1111
01:56:39,576 --> 01:56:41,738
If we deploy
the electromagnetic array,

1112
01:56:41,786 --> 01:56:43,823
there should be
no collateral damage.

1113
01:56:43,955 --> 01:56:44,990
MAN: Here they come!

1114
01:56:52,839 --> 01:56:55,080
I'm doin' this for you, Betty.

1115
01:56:55,258 --> 01:56:59,377
But one way or another, we're
gonna have to prepare for the worst.

1116
01:57:03,850 --> 01:57:05,386
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1117
01:58:48,747 --> 01:58:50,784
<i>I should have killed you.</i>

1118
01:58:51,875 --> 01:58:54,082
And I should have killed you.

1119
01:58:55,545 --> 01:58:57,127
<i>I wish you had.</i>

1120
01:59:03,219 --> 01:59:05,051
I saw her last night.

1121
01:59:07,307 --> 01:59:08,797
Saw her face.

1122
01:59:10,185 --> 01:59:11,550
Brown hair.

1123
01:59:13,605 --> 01:59:15,016
Brown eyes.

1124
01:59:16,399 --> 01:59:18,060
She smiled at me.

1125
01:59:19,402 --> 01:59:21,359
She reached down
and kissed my cheek.

1126
01:59:24,282 --> 01:59:26,569
I can almost remember a small.

1127
01:59:30,914 --> 01:59:33,076
It was like desert flowers.

1128
01:59:35,085 --> 01:59:36,917
Her favorite perfume.

1129
01:59:40,215 --> 01:59:44,083
It's my mother, and I
don't even know her name.

1130
01:59:47,263 --> 01:59:48,503
(SOBBING)

1131
01:59:52,227 --> 01:59:55,970
It's all right, Son.
You go ahead and cry.

1132
02:00:03,113 --> 02:00:04,774
Go ahead and cry.

1133
02:00:08,952 --> 02:00:11,159
Cry. Crying will do you good.

1134
02:00:11,287 --> 02:00:12,823
Don't touch me!

1135
02:00:15,709 --> 02:00:17,950
Maybe once you were my father,

1136
02:00:19,254 --> 02:00:22,042
but you're not now
and you never will be.

1137
02:00:22,132 --> 02:00:23,714
Oh, is that so?

1138
02:00:25,468 --> 02:00:30,133
<i>Well, I got news for you.
I didn't come here to see you.</i>

1139
02:00:31,141 --> 02:00:33,724
I came here to see my son.

1140
02:00:35,103 --> 02:00:36,593
My real son.

1141
02:00:37,272 --> 02:00:39,138
The one inside of you.

1142
02:00:40,191 --> 02:00:43,980
You're nothing
but a superficial shell,

1143
02:00:44,154 --> 02:00:46,441
a husk of flimsy consciousness

1144
02:00:46,656 --> 02:00:49,694
ready to be torn off
at a moment's notice.

1145
02:00:49,909 --> 02:00:53,277
You can think what you like.
I don't care. Just go!

1146
02:00:59,335 --> 02:01:02,544
No, Son. Listen to me
I found a cure.

1147
02:01:03,506 --> 02:01:04,712
For me.

1148
02:01:05,633 --> 02:01:08,000
My cells can transform, too,

1149
02:01:08,344 --> 02:01:10,802
absorb enormous
amounts of energy.

1150
02:01:11,181 --> 02:01:13,639
But, unlike you,
they're unstable.

1151
02:01:14,058 --> 02:01:17,346
<i>Son, I need your strength.</i>

1152
02:01:18,897 --> 02:01:21,013
I gave you life.

1153
02:01:21,441 --> 02:01:24,399
Now you must give it back to me!

1154
02:01:25,403 --> 02:01:30,022
Only a million times
more radiant, more powerful!

1155
02:01:30,116 --> 02:01:33,450
Stop it.
Stop? Stop what?

1156
02:01:33,661 --> 02:01:35,698
Stop what?

1157
02:01:36,539 --> 02:01:40,533
Think about all those men
out there in their uniforms,

1158
02:01:41,294 --> 02:01:44,036
barking and swallowing orders,

1159
02:01:44,339 --> 02:01:47,707
inflicting their petty rule
over the entire globe!

1160
02:01:48,384 --> 02:01:50,921
Think of all the harm
they've done!

1161
02:01:51,554 --> 02:01:53,841
To you! To me!

1162
02:01:54,516 --> 02:01:55,927
To humanity!

1163
02:01:56,893 --> 02:01:59,681
And know this,
that we can make them

1164
02:01:59,729 --> 02:02:02,562
and their flags and their
anthems and their governments

1165
02:02:02,649 --> 02:02:04,890
disappear in a flash!

1166
02:02:05,235 --> 02:02:06,851
You in me.

1167
02:02:07,237 --> 02:02:08,773
I'd rather die.

1168
02:02:10,532 --> 02:02:12,899
Oh, that's your answer?

1169
02:02:13,993 --> 02:02:18,328
Then indeed you shall die
and be reborn

1170
02:02:18,748 --> 02:02:22,161
a hero of the kind
that walked the earth

1171
02:02:22,502 --> 02:02:26,086
long before the pale
religions of civilization

1172
02:02:26,339 --> 02:02:28,922
infected humanity's soul!

1173
02:02:29,092 --> 02:02:31,049
Go!

1174
02:02:40,645 --> 02:02:41,931
(MOCKING)

1175
02:02:46,776 --> 02:02:48,483
Stop your bawling,

1176
02:02:49,445 --> 02:02:52,062
you weak little speck
of human trash.

1177
02:02:59,080 --> 02:03:01,822
All right. I'll go!

1178
02:03:03,585 --> 02:03:06,327
You just watch me go!
Hit it.

1179
02:03:07,005 --> 02:03:08,291
(SNARLING)

1180
02:03:17,640 --> 02:03:19,472
(SCREAMING)

1181
02:03:32,447 --> 02:03:33,653
Hit it again!

1182
02:03:33,740 --> 02:03:35,151
We can't, sir.
There's no power.

1183
02:03:35,199 --> 02:03:37,531
Some kind of
counter-electromagnetic field.

1184
02:03:40,079 --> 02:03:41,661
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1185
02:03:42,665 --> 02:03:45,123
Move in and assault
the target. Move in!

1186
02:03:45,335 --> 02:03:47,872
MAN: Move, move, move!

1187
02:03:49,088 --> 02:03:50,670
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1188
02:03:53,593 --> 02:03:54,958
<i>(MACHINE GUNS FIRING)</i>

1189
02:04:25,041 --> 02:04:26,827
(PANTING)

1190
02:04:35,593 --> 02:04:37,209
(GRUNTING)

1191
02:04:37,261 --> 02:04:40,219
Sir, I've located them
on radar. Pear Lake.

1192
02:04:40,264 --> 02:04:42,221
Call up the task force.

1193
02:04:47,230 --> 02:04:48,391
(GRUNTING)

1194
02:04:49,691 --> 02:04:50,772
Yes.

1195
02:04:57,907 --> 02:04:59,397
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1196
02:05:08,751 --> 02:05:10,412
(HULK ROARING)

1197
02:05:38,114 --> 02:05:39,275
(HULK GROWLING)

1198
02:05:56,382 --> 02:05:58,498
DAVID: That's right. Keep fighting.

1199
02:05:59,802 --> 02:06:03,090
<i>The more you fight,
the more of you I take.</i>

1200
02:06:11,981 --> 02:06:15,895
TECHNICIAN: Strange. We're reading a
phenomenal drop in temperatures there.

1201
02:06:16,444 --> 02:06:18,856
Simultaneous
radiological activity.

1202
02:06:18,946 --> 02:06:21,779
They're absorbing
all the ambient energy.

1203
02:06:29,457 --> 02:06:30,993
BETTY: Relax.

1204
02:06:31,959 --> 02:06:34,826
DAVID: Sleep now, Bruce,
and forget forever.

1205
02:06:35,671 --> 02:06:40,290
Struggle no more
and give me all of your power.

1206
02:06:42,261 --> 02:06:45,344
BRUCE: You think you can
live with it? Take it!

1207
02:06:46,516 --> 02:06:48,632
Take it all!

1208
02:06:52,396 --> 02:06:55,013
<i>DAVID: Oh, yes! Yes!</i>

1209
02:06:56,901 --> 02:06:58,858
(HULK ROARING)

1210
02:07:08,746 --> 02:07:10,236
DAVID: Take it back!

1211
02:07:12,416 --> 02:07:15,033
It's not stopping!

1212
02:07:15,878 --> 02:07:18,119
Take it back!

1213
02:07:22,885 --> 02:07:24,375
(DAVID GROANING)

1214
02:07:34,480 --> 02:07:36,892
Gentlemen, release.

1215
02:07:45,074 --> 02:07:46,735
PILOT ON RADIO:
Gamma charge away.

1216
02:08:11,934 --> 02:08:13,424
Sweet dreams.

1217
02:08:58,022 --> 02:08:59,512
(PHONE RINGING)

1218
02:09:07,406 --> 02:09:09,693
Hello?
ROSS: Betty, is that you?

1219
02:09:09,784 --> 02:09:12,446
<i>Hi, Dad.
I'm glad I caught you.</i>

1220
02:09:12,828 --> 02:09:15,069
I'm glad you called.
Thanks.

1221
02:09:17,500 --> 02:09:20,993
Look, Betty, you and I...

1222
02:09:22,171 --> 02:09:26,165
Well, we both know that Bruce
couldn't have survived that blast.

1223
02:09:26,842 --> 02:09:29,334
But... Well, you know...

1224
02:09:31,305 --> 02:09:33,842
What is it?
Well, you know.

1225
02:09:33,891 --> 02:09:37,134
The usual loonies,
seein' things.

1226
02:09:37,561 --> 02:09:39,518
Only now everything's green.

1227
02:09:41,190 --> 02:09:42,396
Right.

1228
02:09:43,359 --> 02:09:44,770
Look...

1229
02:09:46,237 --> 02:09:48,854
If by some chance
he did survive,

1230
02:09:50,032 --> 02:09:53,741
and he should try to contact
you, try to get in touch,

1231
02:09:55,246 --> 02:09:57,408
you'd tell me, wouldn't you?

1232
02:09:58,499 --> 02:10:01,036
<i>No, I wouldn't.</i>

1233
02:10:02,545 --> 02:10:05,754
<i>But you know as well as I do,
I wouldn't have to.</i>

1234
02:10:06,007 --> 02:10:09,295
I mean, my phones are bugged,
my computer's tapped.

1235
02:10:09,385 --> 02:10:11,296
I'm under surveillance.

1236
02:10:13,973 --> 02:10:15,884
I'll tell you, though,

1237
02:10:16,559 --> 02:10:18,391
that if he were alive,

1238
02:10:18,477 --> 02:10:21,686
I'm the last person
I would want him to come to

1239
02:10:21,772 --> 02:10:25,811
because as much as
I miss him, I...

1240
02:10:27,945 --> 02:10:29,982
I loved him. I...

1241
02:10:33,034 --> 02:10:34,149
Yeah.

1242
02:10:37,496 --> 02:10:39,157
I'm sorry, Betty.

1243
02:10:41,083 --> 02:10:42,573
I am so sorry.

1244
02:10:45,921 --> 02:10:47,457
<i>I know you are.</i>

1245
02:11:21,040 --> 02:11:23,998
(IN SPANISH)

1246
02:11:39,141 --> 02:11:40,427
(IN SPANISH)

1247
02:11:40,768 --> 02:11:42,133
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

1248
02:12:10,172 --> 02:12:11,333
(GOAT BLEATING)

1249
02:12:37,032 --> 02:12:39,524
(HULK ROARING)

